However, I have another potential solution that should address your original issue without the complexity of the workaround I presented earlier. Instead of using `NativeOnMouseButtonUp`, we can handle the entire drag-and-drop operation within the `NativeOnMouseMove` function. This approach does not involve capturing the mouse and will automatically end the drag-and-drop operation when the user releases the mouse button.

Here's the modified code for `NativeOnMouseMove`. Use this in combination with the `NativeOnMouseButtonDown` implementation I provided earlier.

